  "about": {
    "en": {
      "bg": "#948c22",
      "text": "<p>Handcrafted soft-serve Mediterranean gelato, made with heart and honesty.</p><p>We work with local producers and chase remarkable flavours so that every creation carries a memory. Each swirl is meant to bring back a small moment of happiness, something familiar and comforting in a frozen form.</p>",
      "image": "/uploads/1773635788718-image-171.jpg",
      "heading": "About us",
      "intro": "Pâtisserie Rhubarbe opened modestly in October 2010.",
      "body": "<p>Stéphanie Labelle believed there was a gap in Montreal for a boutique pastry shop where you could find fresh products every day, made with good seasonal ingredients. She decided to go for it and open in a charming space on rue De Lanaudière, after 8 years of experience in boutique pastry and restaurant work.</p><p>Julien Joré, a chef with over 20 years of experience, has been helping Stéphanie since the bakery opened. He has been part of the story from the very beginning, but officially became a partner during the expansion. The move to avenue Laurier in May 2017 allowed Comptoir Rhubarbe to open alongside the shop.</p><p>Since then, the rhubarbe boutique has changed its model and moved on July 13, 2025.</p><p>Find us at our new location on Saturdays between 9am and 12pm to pick up orders placed in advance on our website.</p>",
      "address": "1320 rue Charlevoix, Pointe Saint-Charles, Montreal",
      "signoff": "team rhubarbe x"
    },
    "fr": {
      "heading": "À propos de nous",
      "intro": "La pâtisserie Rhubarbe a ouvert modestement en octobre 2010.",
      "body": "<p>Stéphanie Labelle a cru qu'il y avait un besoin à Montréal pour une boutique de pâtisserie où l'on pourrait trouver des produits frais chaque jour, réalisés avec de bons ingrédients de saison. Elle a décidé de se lancer et d'ouvrir dans un charmant espace sur la rue De Lanaudière, après 8 ans d'expérience dans le domaine de la pâtisserie et de la restauration.</p><p>Julien Joré, un chef avec plus de 20 ans d'expérience, aide Stéphanie depuis l'ouverture de la boulangerie. Il fait partie de l'histoire depuis le tout début, mais est devenu officiellement partenaire lors de l'expansion. Le déménagement sur l'avenue Laurier en mai 2017 a permis l'ouverture du Comptoir Rhubarbe aux côtés de la boutique.</p><p>Depuis, la boutique Rhubarbe a changé de modèle et a déménagé le 13 juillet 2025.</p><p>Trouvez-nous à notre nouvel emplacement les samedis entre 9h et 12h pour récupérer les commandes passées à l'avance sur notre site web.</p>",
      "address": "1320 rue Charlevoix, Pointe Saint-Charles, Montréal",
      "signoff": "équipe rhubarbe x"
    }
  },
  "home": {
    "story": {
      "bg": "#333112",
      "text": "<p>This is the story of a lost heritage in a southern village, nestled between the azure sea and the singing cicadas. From Marseille to La Spezia.</p><p>A frozen delight for the long summer days.</p><p>A tribute to a grandmother who loves the sea, the warm sand, and the sweetness of a gelato. It is the story of all those little moments of happiness that belong to each of us, told through frozen flavors with simplicity and honesty.</p><p>To Janine,<br>the cicadas will forever sing your name.</p>",
      "image": "/uploads/1773637015476-image-168.png"
    },
    "editorial": [
      {
        "text": "<p>Our inspiration begins at the market. Following a tradition our chef learned in the south, we start with perfectly ripe seasonal fruit and build every flavour from there. </p><p>Fruit is always the main character. Each sorbet is paired with a creamy Jersey milk gelato, gently infused with spices or native herbs chosen to complement the fruit. The result is a balance where acidity, sweetness, and aromatics meet in harmony.</p>",
        "image": "/uploads/1773636969137-frame-127.png"
      },
      {
        "text": "<p>Our gelato base is made with Jersey cow milk from MC Dairy, a cooperative of small farmers committed to responsible agriculture. Their cows spend the summer grazing in open pasture, producing rich milk while maintaining strong standards for animal care. </p><p>Our eggs come from an Ontario producer known for their naturally golden yolks, laid by free-run hens fed a marigold-rich diet that enhances both colour and nutritional value.</p>",
        "image": "/uploads/1773636975659-frame-128.png"
      },
      {
        "text": "<p>Whenever possible, we source ingredients locally and choose partners who care deeply about the land, their animals, and the quality of what they grow. </p><p>One of our main suppliers is Médiserre, a Montreal-based distributor founded by chefs Andrew and Olivier. They work closely with small Canadian producers to bring exceptional ingredients to kitchens that value seasonality, transparency, and flavour.</p>",
        "image": "/uploads/1773636982745-frame-129.png"
      }
    ],
    "photos": {
      "photo1": "/uploads/1773636989891-frame-120.png",
      "photo2": "/uploads/1773636993465-frame-119.png"
    }
  },
